# Agoge Wrestling Academy

MERN-stack marketing/info website for a wrestling gym. Customers visit to view
info (programs, schedule, staff, pricing) and enroll. Enrollment links out to an
external registration platform (placeholder links for now).

## Design reference

The layout replicates `Beebe/beebetrained-source.html` (extracted from the
client-provided view-source file `Beebe/view-source_beebetrained.com.html`) with
Agoge branding and a black/gold/red Spartan color scheme. See the
`design-system` rule for the palette.

## Structure

- `frontend/` — Vite + React 19 (JSX) single-page site. Builds to `frontend/build/`.
  - `src/data/siteContent.js` — ALL site copy/content lives here (currently placeholders).
  - `src/components/` — one component per page section, each with a co-located `.css` file.
  - `src/index.css` — theme variables, buttons, shared section styles, forms.
- `backend/` — Express 5 + Mongoose scaffold (NOT wired to the frontend yet).
  Routes return 501; contact form uses mailto and reviews use localStorage until wired.
- `deploy/` — `deploy.ps1` (build + upload script) and `nginx-agoge.conf` (server config).
- `Beebe/` — reference source from the site the client wants replicated. Do not modify.
  Excluded from git (root `.gitignore`) — local only.

## Current placeholder status

Business content (address, phone, email, coach names, stats, schedule,
registration URLs, Instagram, logo) is ALL placeholder in `siteContent.js`.
The logo is a temporary Λ text mark until the client provides a real one.

## Planned (pre-launch)

Once real content is finalized: add build-time pre-rendering (static HTML in
`frontend/build/`) plus local SEO work — LocalBusiness JSON-LD schema, localized
copy/keywords, sitemap, proper title/meta descriptions.

## Workflow rules

- Do NOT run `npm run dev` / `node server.js` — the user runs these themselves.
- When work is complete, tell the user which files changed and whether to restart.
- Development is on Windows; production is a DigitalOcean droplet (see below).

## Git / GitHub

Public repo: https://github.com/jacobnaumann/agoge-wrestling-academy (branch `main`).
Root `.gitignore` excludes `Beebe/`, `node_modules/`, `.env`, and `frontend/build/`.

## Production (deployed 2026-07-06)

- Droplet: `agoge-web` (ID 582690044), 204.48.16.139, nyc1, 1GB/1vCPU ($6/mo),
  Ubuntu 24.04, in the client's DO account (agogewrestlingacademyfl@gmail.com,
  project "Agoge"). SSH as `root` with key `~/.ssh/id_ed25519` (jacob-agoge).
- Stack: nginx serves `/var/www/html` (frontend build) and proxies `/api/` to
  Express on port 5000; backend lives at `/root/backend`, runs under PM2 as
  `agoge-api` (resurrects on reboot via systemd). UFW allows OpenSSH + Nginx Full.
- nginx site config: `/etc/nginx/sites-available/agoge` (copy of
  `deploy/nginx-agoge.conf`; default site removed).
- Domain: agogewrestlingacademy.com (+ www), registered and DNS-hosted at
  Cloudflare (client account), proxied (orange cloud) A/CNAME → droplet.
  SSL: Cloudflare edge cert + Cloudflare Origin CA cert on the droplet at
  `/etc/ssl/cloudflare/` (local copies in `deploy/certs/`, gitignored).
  SSL mode Full (strict); Always Use HTTPS on. Origin cert valid 15 years.
- To deploy: run `.\deploy\deploy.ps1` from the repo root (builds the frontend,
  uploads via scp, fixes file perms — Windows scp lands 600/700 — restarts PM2).
- `doctl` CLI is installed (winget) and authenticated against the client account.
- MongoDB not installed — plan is MongoDB Atlas free M0 tier when the backend
  is wired up.
